messages.messageBody:
I just had to share this because I am smiling from ear to ear! Ren
and Kelly do this thing with newbies where they ask them a series of
questions about their hobbies and interests and how much of them the
person learned or got proficient at in school. I was talking about
it with my husband last night and my 13-year-old son came into the
middle of the conversation. He made me this list last night, TOO
COOL!!

Kevin's interests:
computers
drawing, art/ digital art
ice skating
horse back riding
swimming
rollerblading
skateboarding
snowboarding/skiing
traveling to Japan
electronics- cameras, video, computers, ipods
gaming
finding treasures-hidden or buried
scuba diving
rock/mineral hunting
acting- theatre classes
music- playing guitar
baking/cooking
photography
visiting people I met through the internet
building - a shed, barn, anything
owning a petting zoo
film making
running
sewing
HTML coding
landscaping
gardening
fishing
hiking
camping
singing
dancing
writing
reading
Magic
anime/manga
interior designing
cosplay
bowling
movie theatres
japanese
german
spanish
surfing
sealife
exotic animals
woodwork
pottery


WOW, quite the list, eh?


Heidi
